      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PEPPA'S DAUGHTER (1) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 18.77 beating Ascend Jacaranda. Hard to fault her recent form and can win again. NANGAR ARCHIE (4) is better than last start when fifth (18.99) from Box 6 at this track over 330m. Form from his last run is proving strong. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. ROSES RING (7) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 1.5 lengths win at Wagga in a handy 18.65. Draws out wide but likes the trip. Goes very well from this draw with four wins and two minor placings from nine starts. Has definite claims. WESTSIDE BLISS (3) is worth including after a top-three finish most recently.",
